\cot^2 x+\sec^2x=\frac{\cos^2x}{\sin^2x}+\frac 1{\cos^2x}=\frac{\cos^4x+\sin^2x}{\cos^2x\sin^2x}
\tan^2x+\csc^2x=\frac {\sin^2x}{\cos^2x}+\frac 1{\sin^2x}=\frac{\sin^4x+\cos^2x}{\cos^2x\sin^2x}
\cos^4x+\sin^2x=\sin^4x+\cos^2x
\sin^2x+\cos^2x=1
\csc^2x-\cot^2x=1=\sec^2x-\tan^2x
1+\cot ^2x = \dfrac{\sin^2x+\cos^2x}{\sin^2x} = \csc ^2x
1+\tan ^2x = \dfrac{\cos^2x + \sin^2x}{\cos^2x} = \sec ^2x
cot^2(x) + 1 = csc^2(x)
tan^2(x) + 1 = sec^2(x)
\cot ^2x+\sec ^2x=csc^2(x)-1+tan^2(x) + 1=tan^2(x)+csc^2(x)
\cot ^2x+\sec ^2x=tan^2(x)+csc^2(x)
